name: Hardy
summary: Entertainment news headlines reveal an upcoming HARDY concert at Mississippi State University on September 12th. In related news, actors Aaron Taylor-Johnson and Tom Hardy have signed on for the Jo Nesbo film "Blood on Snow." Additionally, Boston's 98.5 The Sports Hub is experiencing changes, including the "Toucher and Hardy" show undergoing a shake-up. Tom Hardy's crime thriller has become a streaming hit despite its box office disappointment. Bucknell University's volleyball team set a program record in digs under Coach Hardy's leadership. BioMarin, a pharmaceutical company, anticipates significant growth in sales. "Idol" winner Laine Hardy is engaged and expecting his first child. Hardy is also ranked among the greatest film actors in a list of 11 notable performances. Cary Fukunaga's "Blood on Snow," featuring Hardy and Taylor-Johnson, is scheduled to begin filming this fall.

name: Grandparents Day
summary: Grandparents Day is celebrated on September 8th of every year, and different organizations and publications have dedicated articles to honoring this special occasion. The Deseret News provides an introspective piece titled "What kind of grandparent are you?" that encourages readers to consider their role as grandparents and how they can positively impact the lives of their grandchildren. Parade Magazine offers a collection of "45 Sweet Grandparents Day Poems" that can be used to express love and appreciation for grandparents. The Kankakee Daily Journal shares a personal account in "A TAYLOR-MADE LIFE: Happy Grandparents Day" that highlights the special bond between a grandmother and her grandson. The National Day Calendar provides a comprehensive list of September 8th observances, including National Grandparents Day, which is also accompanied by other days such as National Hug Your Hound Day and Star Trek Day. The Sisters of Providence of Saint Mary-of-the-Woods offers a heartfelt piece titled "Celebrating Grandparents’ Day" that reflects on the invaluable role grandparents play in families and communities. The City of Warren announces its "GRANDPARENTS’ DAY CELEBRATION 2024" event, which includes activities and entertainment for grandparents and their families. NorthJersey.com suggests "a few things to do for your grandparents" on this special day, emphasizing the importance of spending quality time together. USA TODAY encourages readers to "Celebrate Grandma and Grandpa on National Grandparents Day" by sharing stories, photos, and special messages. Mountain Lake PBS provides resources for celebrating the holiday, including videos, activities, and educational content. Finally, the United States Army shares the personal experience of a deputy garrison commander who reflects on Grandparents Day and the selfless service of grandparents in the military.
